## Pull request overview

Implements support for collector-level write sequences (`init_writes`, `pre_poll`) for I2C/SPI/I3C collectors, enabling device initialization and per-poll trigger writes as described in issue #156.

**Changes:**
- Adds `WriteStep` config parsing/validation (including `ByteValue` to accept single-byte or byte-array YAML values).
- Introduces `MetricWriter` / `MetricWriterFactory` and protocol-specific writer implementations (I2C/SPI/I3C).
- Integrates `init_writes` (post-connect/reconnect) and `pre_poll` (before each poll cycle) into the collector loop.

### Reviewed changes

Copilot reviewed 8 out of 8 changed files in this pull request and generated 5 comments.

<details>
<summary>Show a summary per file</summary>

| File | Description |
| ---- | ----------- |
| src/config.rs | Adds write-step types, deserialization, collector fields, and validation logic. |
| src/config_tests.rs | Adds unit tests for write-step parsing/validation. |
| src/reader/mod.rs | Introduces writer traits and extends factory implementation to create writers per protocol. |
| src/reader/i2c/mod.rs | Adds I2C write support and an I2C metric writer implementation. |
| src/reader/spi/mod.rs | Adds SPI metric writer implementation for command-based write steps. |
| src/reader/i3c/mod.rs | Adds I3C metric writer implementation using address resolution + bus lock. |
| src/collector.rs | Executes `init_writes` and `pre_poll` within collector lifecycle, with failure handling/reconnect logic. |
| src/collector_tests.rs | Updates test collector config and factory traits to compile with new writer factory abstraction. |
</details>






